{"mode":"human","topic":"What is stereotype threat in STEM? Should we address it? And how?","opinion":"Stereotype threat in STEM is a formidable issue that warrants our undivided attention, and I firmly believe we should indeed address it through multifaceted strategies that are sensitive to the nuances of the plumber's experience as well as the broader societal context.  Let's begin by understanding what stereotype threat truly entails. It's not merely prejudice, though that undoubtedly plays a role; it's a psychological phenomenon where individuals from stereotyped groups fear confirming negative stereotypes about their abilities. Imagine a young man named Marco, a plumber in Naples, constantly reminded through his education system and even casual conversations that he doesn't quite measure up to the stereotypical image of the " ,
